@startuml
title How Prometheus Metrics Work

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2

actor "User" as user
participant "React SPA\n:7070" as spa
participant "Order Service\n:8001" as order
database "In-Memory\nMetrics" as mem
participant "Prometheus\n:9090" as prom
database "Time-Series\nDatabase" as tsdb
participant "Grafana\n:3000" as grafana

== 1. User Action Generates Metrics ==

user -> spa : Click "Place Order"
spa -> order : POST /orders
order -> order : Handle request
order -> mem : orders_total.inc()\norder_amount.observe(29.99)\norder_processing_seconds.observe(0.05)
order --> spa : { order_id: "abc123", status: "queued" }
spa --> user : Show order confirmation

== 2. Prometheus Scrapes Metrics (every 15s) ==

prom -> order : GET /metrics
mem --> prom : # TYPE orders_total counter\norders_total{status="queued"} 42\norders_total{status="failed"} 3\n# TYPE order_amount_dollars histogram\norder_amount_dollars_bucket{le="50"} 28\n...
prom -> tsdb : Store values with timestamp

note over prom
  Prometheus **pulls** metrics
  from each service.
  Services do NOT push.
end note

== 3. Grafana Queries Prometheus ==

grafana -> prom : PromQL: rate(orders_total[1m])
prom -> tsdb : Query time-series data
tsdb --> prom : [{t: 12:00, v: 0.5}, {t: 12:01, v: 0.8}, ...]
prom --> grafana : JSON response with data points
grafana -> grafana : Render graph

user -> grafana : View dashboard
grafana --> user : Display charts and panels

@enduml
